paragraphs.text:
%md
Extra spark functions
---------------------

def transposeUDF(transDF: DataFrame, transBy: Seq[String]): DataFrame = {
  val (cols, types) = transDF.dtypes.filter{ case (c, _) => !transBy.contains(c)}.unzip
  require(types.distinct.size == 1)      

  val kvs = explode(array(
    cols.map(c => struct(lit(c).alias("column_name"), col(c).alias("column_value"))): _*
  ))

  val byExprs = transBy.map(col(_))

  transDF
    .select(byExprs :+ kvs.alias("_kvs"): _*)
    .select(byExprs ++ Seq($"_kvs.column_name", $"_kvs.column_value"): _*)
}

paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT DISTINCT anage.`Common name`, anage.`Maximum longevity (yrs)`, anage.`Adult weight (g)` / 1000.0 as Weight_KG 
FROM anage 
WHERE (anage.Phylum like "Chordata") AND (anage.Class like "Mammalia") AND (anage.`Adult weight (g)` IS NOT NULL) AND (anage.`Adult weight (g)` > 1000.0) AND (anage.`Maximum longevity (yrs)` > 1) ORDER BY anage.`Maximum longevity (yrs)` DESC

paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT DISTINCT anage.`Common name`, anage.`Maximum longevity (yrs)`, log(anage.`Adult weight (g)` / 1000.0) as Weight_LOG 
FROM anage 
WHERE (anage.Phylum like "Chordata") AND (anage.Class like "Mammalia") AND (anage.`Adult weight (g)` IS NOT NULL) AND (anage.`Adult weight (g)` > 1000.0) AND (anage.`Maximum longevity (yrs)` > 1) ORDER BY anage.`Maximum longevity (yrs)` DESC

paragraphs.text:
%md
Apoptosis & DNA repair [+cell cycle regulation]
------------------

%md
GO terms associated with apoptosis and DNA repair were upregulated in whale species we examined, especially in a gray whale:
GO:0045738 (Genes: RS3; F6V436; G1MF88; W5PPH6) negative regulation of DNA repair.
GO:1902546 (Genes: APN2; RS3; B6K234; S9VT48) positive regulation of DNA N-glycosylase activity.
GO:1902231 (Genes: PIAS4; NEMF; NACC2; MTCH2; FBH1) positive regulation of intrinsic apoptotic signaling pathway in response to DNA damage.
GO:0032079 (Genes: AKT1; DDX11; HSP77; KPCD; RAD54) positive regulation of endodeoxyribonuclease activity.
GO:2001272 (Genes: BNIP3; EIF3M) positive regulation of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity involved in execution phase of apoptosis.
GO:1905053 (Genes: F168A; RS3; F7IEX3; H2QZR3) positive regulation of base-excision repair.
GO:0010941 (Genes: CRYAB; DRONC; EF1D) (Calcium-binding mitochondrial carrier protein SCaMC-1 isoform X1) regulation of cell death - high rank in GW.
GO:0006977 DNA damage response, signal transduction by p53 class mediator resulting in cell cycle arrest     484    1129    500    1461    900    1610    1088
GO:0043517    positive regulation of DNA damage response, signal transduction by p53 class mediator
p53:
GO:1901796    regulation of signal transduction by p53 class mediator. !! long-lived >> short-lived
250    516    246    150    389    1666    3251
442    932    428    346    729    3234    6165
In GW and MW higher rank than BW, in NMR even higher, In Human lower, in mouse and cow low ranks.

msg.data:
<script>

var layout = {
  title: 'Hypoxia liver (by ranks)',
  annotations: [],
  margin: {
    l: 700,
    r: 125,
    t: 300,
    b: 50
  },
  width: 1200,
  height: 500,
  xaxis: {
    side: 'top'
  },
  yaxis: {
    side: 'left',
    autorange: 'reversed',
  }
};
var xValues = ["gray_whale_liver","bowhead_whale_liver","minke_liver","cow_totalRNA_liver","cow_mRNA_liver","NMR_liver","human_liver","mouse_totalRNA_liver","mouse_mRNA_liver"]
var yValues =  ["regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to hypoxia","negative regulation of hypoxia-induced intrinsic apoptotic signaling pathway","hypoxia-inducible factor-1alpha signaling pathway","negative regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to hypoxia"]
var zValues =  [[5.23,5.81,5.18,8.67,8.56,5.82,6.17,8.75,8.67],[6.05,5.67,5.89,6.72,6.69,8.04,6.92,6.7,7.02],[7.52,7.33,7.22,8.6,8.4,8.28,8.49,8.54,8.53],[7.98,8.18,7.6,7.96,8.05,8.33,8.58,8.43,8.54]]
var aValues =  [[186.0,332.0,178.0,5836.0,5216.0,336.0,477.0,6328.0,5815.0],[425.0,291.0,363.0,827.0,808.0,3104.0,1016.0,812.0,1124.0],[1837.0,1527.0,1371.0,5426.0,4435.0,3946.0,4867.0,5103.0,5063.0],[2930.0,3560.0,1992.0,2853.0,3126.0,4156.0,5315.0,4596.0,5101.0]]

for ( var i = 0; i < yValues.length; i++ ) {
  for ( var j = 0; j < xValues.length; j++ ) {
    var currentValue = zValues[i][j];
    if (currentValue != 0.0) {
      var textColor = 'white';
    }else{
      var textColor = 'black';
    }
    var result = {
      xref: 'x1',
      yref: 'y1',
      x: xValues[j],
      y: yValues[i],
      text: aValues[i][j],
      font: {
        family: 'Arial',
        size: 5,
        color: 'rgb(50, 171, 96)'
      },
      showarrow: false,
      font: {
        color: textColor
      }
    };
    layout.annotations.push(result);
  }
}

var data = [{
   x: xValues,
   y: yValues,
   z: zValues,
   
   colorscale: 'RdBu',  showscale: false ,
   type: 'heatmap' , reversescale: true
 }];
 Plotly.newPlot('hyp', data, layout);
</script>

paragraphs.text:
%md
Cellular components
-------------------

%md
BP!!! GO:1990000 amyloid fibril formation - high in GW.
528       1117     939     342     2577     3016     1604.  (NOTE: CC - Amyloid-beta complex similar) (cyclin-dependent kinase inhibitor 2A; gene: ARF)
Cellular components ranks are much more consistent and across species, and especially across whales.
As expected, the highest ranks were observed for basic cellular components. Extracellular exosome category exhibits the top most highest rank in all species. 
GO:0045263 proton-transporting ATP synthase complex, coupling factor F(o) is high in GW, similar to BP GOs.
GO:0005925 focal adhesion high in all whales. Lipoprotein complexes high in whales.

Hemoglobin complex - higher ranks in whales.  hypoxia
cytoplasmic side of lysosomal membrane - GW and BW similar high ranks, MW lower ranks (2 orders of magnitude).

%md
LAG-s (Longevity Associated Genes)
==================================

%md
Load LAG-s
-----------

val mouse_pro_genes =  spark.readTSV(az("lags" + "/by_genes/" + "genes_pro_longevity_mouse.tsv"), headers = true)
val mouse_anti_genes =  spark.readTSV(az("lags" + "/by_genes/" + "genes_anti_longevity_mouse.tsv"), headers = true)

val fly_pro_genes =  spark.readTSV(az("lags" + "/by_genes/" + "genes_pro_longevity_fly.tsv"), headers = true)
val fly_anti_genes =  spark.readTSV(az("lags" + "/by_genes/" + "genes_anti_longevity_fly.tsv"), headers = true)


val worm_pro_genes =  spark.readTSV(az("lags" + "/by_genes/" + "genes_pro_longevity_worm.tsv"), headers = true)
val worm_anti_genes =  spark.readTSV(az("lags" + "/by_genes/" + "genes_anti_longevity_worm.tsv"), headers = true)

mouse_pro_genes.registerTempTable("mouse_pro_genes")
fly_pro_genes.registerTempTable("fly_pro_genes")
worm_pro_genes.registerTempTable("worm_pro_genes")

mouse_anti_genes.registerTempTable("mouse_anti_genes")
fly_anti_genes.registerTempTable("fly_anti_genes")
worm_anti_genes.registerTempTable("worm_anti_genes")

%md
Count LAGs
-----------

import org.apache.spark.sql._
val fNames: List[String] = mouse_pro_genes.columns.filter(c=>c.contains("identity")).toList
val renamings = fNames.map(c=>c ->c.replace("max(identity_", "").replace(")", "") )
val newNames = renamings.map(_._2)
val counts = newNames.map(c=> count(c))

def prepareCounts(df: DataFrame, species: String) = {
 val f = fNames.map(c=> new ColumnName(c))
 val toSelect = $"Entrez Gene ID"::newNames.map(new ColumnName(_))
 val df2 = df.rename(renamings.toMap).select(toSelect:_*).withColumn("species", lit(species))
 df2.groupBy($"species", $"Entrez Gene ID").agg(counts.head, counts.tail:_*)    
}

def summarize(mouse: DataFrame, fly: DataFrame, worm: DataFrame) = prepareCounts(mouse, "mouse").union(prepareCounts(fly, "fly")).union(prepareCounts(worm, "worm")).groupBy("species").sum(newNames.map("count("+_+")"):_*).rename(newNames.map(n=>(s"sum(count($n))")->n).toMap)
